5.(c).
To write a c code to open a file, read its contents, and close it.

C code:

#include <unistd.h>
#include <fcntl.h>
int main() {
    char buffer[100];(A buffer is simply a temporary storage area.)
    int fd = open("student.txt", O_RDONLY);(O_RDONLY is about readonly acces for student.txt file)
    read(fd, buffer, 100);(fd=file description,array,limit)
    close(fd);(closing the file description)
    return 0;
}
